dashboard.definition:
{
	"title": "Add Event Length",
	"description": "",
	"inputs": {
		"input_time": {
			"type": "input.timerange",
			"title": "",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "-7d@h,now",
				"token": "time"
			}
		},
		"input_span": {
			"type": "input.dropdown",
			"title": "Select time span for chart",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "30min",
				"items": [
					{
						"label": "5min",
						"value": "5min"
					},
					{
						"label": "15min",
						"value": "15min"
					},
					{
						"label": "30min",
						"value": "30min"
					},
					{
						"label": "1hr",
						"value": "1hr"
					},
					{
						"label": "6hr",
						"value": "6hr"
					},
					{
						"label": "1d",
						"value": "1d"
					},
					{
						"label": "1w",
						"value": "1w"
					}
				],
				"prefix": "span=",
				"token": "selected_span"
			}
		},
		"input_field": {
			"type": "input.dropdown",
			"title": "Select field",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "index",
				"items": [
					{
						"label": "index",
						"value": "index"
					},
					{
						"label": "sourcetype",
						"value": "sourcetype"
					},
					{
						"label": "host",
						"value": "host"
					},
					{
						"label": "source",
						"value": "source"
					}
				],
				"token": "selected_field"
			}
		}
	},
	"defaults": {
		"dataSources": {
			"ds.search": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			},
			"ds.spl2": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			}
		},
		"visualizations": {
			"global": {
				"showProgressBar": true
			}
		}
	},
	"visualizations": {
		"viz_markdown": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "# Problem statement \n\nSplunk either charges by vCPU or by license usage. Whichever method is used license reporting goes into the `license.log` file and usage it attributed to `sourcetype`, `host` and `index`. This is sufficent for Splunk to assess licence usage and attribute to high level sources. Occasionally you may wish to further breakdown how license usage is being consumed, perphaps attributing to multiple dimensions for instance this host and this sourcetype. \n\nAlso sourcetypes like `stash`, or indexes like `_internal` do not write any data to license.log and it therefore difficult to judge how many MB has been ingested in these cases.\n\n## Existing solution\nYou can write searches on `license.log` for crude roll ups per sourcetype and index. Alternatively you can estimate usage by computing the average len of your events and multipling by the number of events. \n\n# Alternative approach \nWith the introduction of `INGEST_EVAL` we can add an indexed field that contains the length of the `_raw` string and then use `tstats` to compute license usage accurately and effciently at large over long durations with far more complex logic.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. Set the `default` sourcetype to catch very event passing through the ingestion pipeline\n1. Set the `transform` to have a name that comes last in the evaluation logic\n1. Use `INGEST_EVAL` to compute the length of `_raw` and apply to the field `event_length`\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_chart": {
			"type": "splunk.column",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_chart"
			},
			"options": {
				"stackMode": "stacked",
				"legendTruncation": "ellipsisMiddle"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "Detailed volume over time"
		},
		"viz_conf_transforms": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### transforms.conf\n\nFrom `default/transforms.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n# Add an indexed field holding len(_raw). Must be the LAST transform in the\n# chain so nothing else changes _raw after we measure it.\n[add_event_length-get_raw_length]\nINGEST_EVAL= _event_length=len(_raw)\n```\n"
			}
		}
	},
	"dataSources": {
		"ds_chart": {
			"name": "Detailed volume over time",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "| tstats sum(_event_length) as total_ingestion \n    where index=* \n    by _time $selected_field$ $selected_span$ \n| xyseries _time $selected_field$ total_ingestion",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "$time.earliest$",
					"latest": "$time.latest$"
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"layout": {
		"globalInputs": [
			"input_time",
			"input_span",
			"input_field"
		],
		"layoutDefinitions": {
			"layout_1": {
				"type": "grid",
				"options": {
					"width": 1440,
					"height": 250
				},
				"structure": [
					{
						"item": "viz_markdown",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 900
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_chart",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 900
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_transforms",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 900,
							"w": 1440,
							"h": 480
						}
					}
				]
			}
		},
		"options": {
			"submitButton": false
		},
		"tabs": {
			"items": [
				{
					"label": "New tab",
					"layoutId": "layout_1"
				}
			]
		}
	},
	"applicationProperties": {
		"hideEdit": false,
		"hideExport": false
	}
}
